snippet.textDisplay:
Farwa Rauf wrote this, but it seemed so good that I wanted to spread it.


I am not going into theories here I am just talking about lyrics and mv to show what is the message Yoongi wants us to get:

There are two perspectives here.

1) YOONGI, a young kid with a dream: Yoongi wanted to gain fame from his music so he worked hard for that. Now that he's reached the pinnacle of his fame he has realized that it is very lonely up there and you know how they say that once you reach the top there's only one way down. So he is anxious and scared of falling, he wants to run away from the anxiety and the shadows of people wanting him/ BTS to fall. Now that he has achieved everything he wants to run away from being rich, a rockstar, a rapstar and all that.



2) SUGA: After @ the song becomes aggressive as if it is Suga (his stage persona) talking to Yoongi, the real artist. He tells him that no matter what he does he can't run away from him. Hence the lyrics "I am you, you are me." etc That with success comes backlash and anxiety so you can't run away from all that now. It's like Yoongi is trying to accept the highs and lows of being Suga.





Also he talks about "We are one body sometimes we will clash" @ @ he is fighting a battle within himself. Yoongi wanted to be a songwriter because he wasn't fond of attention but now he is one of the most famous hence scrutinized person in the world. So there's a war within what he wanted to be and what has become of him.



Like the m/v can be divided into 3 parts.
In the first part he is standing still talking about his dream then he starts running ( hard work)

In the second part once he stops running he finds himself on the stage @ @ (his hard work payed off)

In the last part, he sees himself as everything he always wanted to be (all eyes on him) but now he just wants to be himself.
Again he comes to the conclusion that he can't escape that now. The fame is a part of him. Although he feels lonely he has to admit it that in order to gain something you have to lose something like @ @ he says "you'll be at ease if you admit it too."


I am pretty sure he is thankful of ARMY and fame he got but I am glad he touched this aspect of fame and made people realize that fame is much more than just being a rockstar, a rapstar, a king and being rich.

snippet.textDisplay:
THEORY:
At 2:12 seconds when suga comes out of the crowd, it changes perspective and Yoongi isn't rapping anymore, it is his "Shadow"
As he says stuff like "Yea you are me, I'm you, now do you know", "We are one body, sometimes we will clash" and importantly, "You can never break me off, this you must know" This shows that Yoongi (Who I also think is representing BTS as a whole in this song) is being confronted by his shadows, which is all the fear and loneliness that he feels after succeeding so high (Suggesting how he can never truly be looked at as a normal person anymore, the fame has put them all on such a tall pedestal and the higher they go, the scarier it is. The shadow is also basically telling him that he must stop running away from his shadow because it will always be a part of him, Yoongi/BTS need to face their fears and shadows in order to stop being lonely and scared. :)
